'''Richard Max Josef Bletschacher''' (* October 23, 1936 in [[F<U+00FC>ssen|F<U+00FC>ssen am Lech]]) is a German writer and dramatic advisor. 

Bletschacher studied law, philosophy and literature in [[Munich]], [[Heidelberg]], [[Paris]] and [[Vienna]]. From 1982 to 1996 he was chief dramatic advisor at [[Vienna State Opera]]. He wrote and translated libretti, spectacles, lyrics, novellas, children's books and academc texts on music.

Richard Bletschacher lives in [[Vienna]] and [[Drosendorf-Zissersdorf|Drosendorf an der Thaya]].

